Datatype is nothing but the type of data that we have.

In Java,We have two different categories of datatypes:

1) primitive datatype : used to store simple values. They store the actual values.

We have 8 different primitive data types:

byte --> 1 byte 
short --> 2 bytes 
int --> 4 bytes 
long --> 8 bytes 
float --> 4 bytes 
double --> 8 bytes
char --> 2 byte (unicode characterset hence 2 bytes)
boolean -->  1 bit (true or false)

2)  non primitive/reference datatypes: used to store complex values. Store reference (or) memory address that point to the location
of the object in the memory rather than the actual values.

- strings
- classes
- enums & collection 
- interfaces